{
  "texts": [
    "Enhancing cross-modal learning in federated settings enables models to leverage insights from different data types effectively.",
    "In addition, optimizing the performance of multi-modal models like GPT-4o in FL frameworks is vital, particularly for communication efficiency and computational demands.In FedFM, the demand for high computational resources on FL client devices poses a persistent challenge.",
    "Despite strategies to mitigate this, it remains an open issue.",
    "Approaches such as model splitting [258] and model compression [259] have been proposed.",
    "In addition, efforts are made to develop lighter models and more efficient training algorithms [260] that are less taxing on device resources."
  ]
}